# TAOD-VEGA: Task-Aware Object Detection with Semantic Relevance Scoring

**Team Voltrons — NIT Patna | DVCon India 2026 | Submission 650**
*Rachit Kumar · Mohd Sameer · Om Vats*

---

## Overview

Conventional object detectors (YOLOv8, Faster-RCNN, SSD) identify *every* object in a scene without understanding intent. For robotics and edge AI, only **one object matters** — the one most relevant to the current task.

**TAOD-VEGA** accepts a natural-language task description alongside an RGB image and outputs the *single most task-appropriate object* in the scene. The system runs entirely on a Genesys-2 FPGA board using the VEGA RISC-V soft-IP processor and a custom CNNA (Convolutional Neural Network Accelerator) RTL core.

> **Example:** Image: kitchen counter with wine glass, cup, plate, fork, bottle.
> Task: `"Serve a drink"` → **wine_glass** | bbox: (245, 130, 80, 120) | score: 0.94

### Targets
| Metric | Target | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Latency | < 50 ms | On FPGA (VEGA + CNNA) |
| Power | < 5 W | Kintex-7 total |
| Top-1 Accuracy | ≥ 60% | Weighted over 14 tasks |

---

## Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                        TAOD-VEGA SYSTEM                              │
│                                                                      │
│   INPUT: RGB Image (320×320)  +  Task String ("Serve a drink")       │
│                       │                    │                         │
│          ┌────────────▼──────────┐         │                         │
│          │    STAGE 1: DETECT   │         │                         │
│          │    YOLOv8-nano       │         │                         │
│          │    INT8 on CNNA RTL  │         │                         │
│          │    → N detections    │         │                         │
│          └────────────┬──────────┘         │                         │
│                       │                    │                         │
│          ┌────────────▼────────────────────▼──────┐                  │
│          │         STAGE 2: SCORE                 │                  │
│          │  TinyBERT Dual-Encoder (INT8, VEGA CPU)│                  │
│          │  task_emb = encode(task_string)        │                  │
│          │  obj_emb  = encode(class_label)        │                  │
│          │  score = α·cos_sim + (1-α)·det_conf    │                  │
│          └─────────────────┬──────────────────────┘                  │
│                            │ scored + ranked detections               │
│          ┌─────────────────▼──────────┐                              │
│          │     STAGE 3: SELECT       │                              │
│          │  Top-1 Ranked Selector    │                              │
│          │  threshold = 0.30         │                              │
│          └─────────────────┬──────────┘                              │
│                            │                                          │
│   OUTPUT: class_label + bbox + relevance_score  (UART / Python)      │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

HARDWARE STACK (Genesys-2 Kintex-7 XC7K325T):
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  VEGA RISC-V (RV32IM)  ←→  CNNA RTL     │
  │    cnna_driver.c            cnna_top.v   │
  │    yolov8_runtime.c         systolic_array.v (16×16 INT8)
  │    tinybert_runtime.c       axi4_dma.v   │
  │    nms_fixed.c              csr_regbank.v│
  │                             weight_buffer.v (512 KB BRAM)
  │                             activ_buffer.v (256 KB ping-pong)
  └──────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Clone and install
git clone https://github.com/nitpatna/taod-vega
cd taod-vega
pip install -e .

# 2. Run the CLI demo (downloads YOLOv8n + TinyBERT automatically)
python demo/cli_demo.py --image data/sample_images/kitchen.jpg \
                        --task "Serve a drink"

# 3. Launch the Gradio web demo
python demo/app.py
# → Open http://localhost:7860

# 4. Run all unit tests
pytest tests/ -v --tb=short

# 5. Full 14-task benchmark (requires COCO val2017)
python data/download_coco.py --dest data/
python demo/cli_demo.py --benchmark \
  --coco-val-dir data/val2017 \
  --coco-ann-file data/annotations/instances_val2017.json
```

